snippet.textDisplay: Honestly the only thing I hate about the car is its greatest feature: the engine position. While putting it so far back is a great weight distributor, it looks like a pain to work on. Just doing spark plugs looks like an engine out deal (slight exaggeration, but you get my point). Please tell me maintenance isnt that big of a deal because honestly I'd get a Trans Am if the maintenance is as easy as my Mustang or a Corvette. I'd get a catfish but a bat is cooler (its a bird but the front of a WS6 reminds me of a bats nose)

snippet.textDisplay:
Not a fan of the 4th gen ( 2nd/3rd gen fan ) but it was a great budget performamce car and really well sorted. The SS was faster around Miford ( GM's test track with the Lutz Ring ) than the Z51 equipped Corvette contemporary.

LT1 powered cars were good but when the LS1 cars rolled out and in SS trim there wasnt a better domestic performance car for the money.

snippet.textDisplay: He missed all the reasons this particular engine was so good(98-2002). It has a HUGE aftermarket. And aside from the aluminum block/aluminum head combo, these LS1’s had pretty good bottom ends. These were 6 bolt main blocks. The bottom end can take MASSIVE amounts of power. Just massive. Compare that to the the LT1 in the 93-97 Camaros which had a 2 bolt main unless(most) unless you were lucky enough to get the LT4 Vette motor.
